main event: An 18-year-old male observer reported seeing a bright, elongated light hovering in the sky at an estimated altitude of 500 feet in Santa Ana, California on August 6, 1965.
interesting points: The light was observed for approximately 3-4 minutes before suddenly disappearing.
The report was forwarded to the Air Force through normal channels, and the Air Force classified the sighting as unidentified.
The report contains several photographs, including images of a rural landscape, a vehicle's dashboard view, and what appears to be an unidentified aerial object in the sky.
The photographs are marked as 'FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY' and are from the Foreign Technology Division of the Air Force.
The report also includes a handwritten note that says 'Williams Aug 6 813 3'.
